59
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:22,029
A young leader.

60
00:05:26,033 --> 00:05:28,452
Are that prosecutor
and female reporter still alive?

61
00:05:29,954 --> 00:05:31,706
Isn't that wrong?

62
00:05:33,165 --> 00:05:34,208
I'm sorry, sir.

63
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:39,255
Don't be sorry.

64
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:41,757
I hate it when people are sorry.

65
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:45,720
I'll take care of them soon.

66
00:05:47,596 --> 00:05:48,723
Do you mean it?

67
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:57,273
If they manage to survive again,
you will have to stand in

68
00:05:57,606 --> 00:05:59,316
for that target, okay?

69
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:21,964
I've gathered some material on the case.

70
00:06:22,048 --> 00:06:24,592
I also snuck a copy
of the case record just in case.

71
00:06:25,968 --> 00:06:27,178
Isn't that illegal?

72
00:06:28,345 --> 00:06:30,097
Look who's talking.

73
00:06:41,484 --> 00:06:42,735
What on earth?

74
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:45,863
They came by.

75
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:59,335
They're gone.
All the records I've gathered.

76
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:02,755
I doubt this was the only place
they ransacked.

77
00:07:22,066 --> 00:07:23,192
Who are you?

78
00:07:29,365 --> 00:07:31,075
Are you Mr. Gong Daechul?

79
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:33,160
Do you know me?

80
00:07:34,078 --> 00:07:35,496
Where's Song Suhyeon?

81
00:07:38,165 --> 00:07:40,876
Out of the blue?
I don't know where he is. How would I?

82
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:46,590
There's no trace of him packing.
It means he didn't plan on hiding.

83
00:07:57,601 --> 00:07:58,769
Too bad.

84
00:08:01,021 --> 00:08:04,608
If you don't know,
it'll be a headache for both of us.

85
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:16,745
I can't visit him?

86
00:08:16,954 --> 00:08:19,165
That's what the law says, mister.

87
00:08:19,248 --> 00:08:22,126
In exceptional cases, the prison chief

88
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:24,461
may prohibit visitations.

89
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:26,839
Look how gutsy you are,

90
00:08:26,922 --> 00:08:29,508
explaining the law to a prosecutor.

91
00:08:32,428 --> 00:08:33,679
A prosecutor?

92
00:08:46,108 --> 00:08:48,360
- The punishment room?
- Yes.

93
00:08:48,444 --> 00:08:49,778
There was a report

94
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:53,282
that he took narcotics
that were smuggled in.

95
00:08:53,365 --> 00:08:56,076
He's in solitary
until the investigation is over.

96
00:08:56,619 --> 00:08:59,163
So you locked him up
and are forbidding visitations?

97
00:08:59,246 --> 00:09:02,666
If anyone's unhappy with it,
they'll file an administrative litigation.

98
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:04,668
To revoke his punishment.

99
00:09:07,087 --> 00:09:10,174
Did the prosecution ask for a prohibition
on visitation regarding this case?

100
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:12,843
I doubt it.

101
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:15,930
You haven't even made an official request
to investigate it.

102
00:09:17,848 --> 00:09:19,683
I have full authority over this matter.

103
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:23,020
So the prison is conducting
the investigation? And you are the judge?

104
00:09:23,103 --> 00:09:24,396
No.

105
00:09:24,563 --> 00:09:26,482
Well, that's...

106
00:09:26,565 --> 00:09:28,192
Let me make it clear for you.

107
00:09:28,275 --> 00:09:31,028
Criminally speaking,
you're abusing your authority here.

108
00:09:31,111 --> 00:09:33,364
You are keeping an inmate
from exercising his rights.

109
00:09:33,447 --> 00:09:36,408
You want me to list all the ways
you're violating criminal law?

110
00:09:38,619 --> 00:09:39,912
What do you say?

111
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:47,670
My point here is,
let me speak with Lee Changwoo in person.

112
00:09:48,754 --> 00:09:50,589
What's taking him so long?

113
00:09:51,173 --> 00:09:52,925
What is this, a family reunion?

114
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:55,594
Ten minutes should be enough for a visit.

115
00:09:58,722 --> 00:10:00,432
Why would it snow in April?

116
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,978
So much for a car wash.

117
00:10:04,728 --> 00:10:06,188
He refused to meet you.

118
00:10:07,439 --> 00:10:09,733
Did you specifically tell him my name?

119
00:10:09,817 --> 00:10:10,943
Yes.

120
00:10:11,735 --> 00:10:12,861
Gosh.

121
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:15,906
Let's go to the punishment room.

122
00:10:18,075 --> 00:10:19,576
I'll go there myself.

123
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:25,081
What?

124
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:27,501
Read this first.

125
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:31,796
What is this?

126
00:10:32,381 --> 00:10:34,717
Inmate 1014 wrote it himself.

127
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:40,347
PROSECUTOR SONG, I DON'T WANT TO MEET YOU
DON'T EVER COME AGAIN

128
00:10:40,431 --> 00:10:43,434
Prosecutor, what should we do?

129
00:10:43,517 --> 00:10:47,104
It's not like we can force him
to meet you against his will.

130
00:10:52,401 --> 00:10:54,778
Don't smirk, all right?

131
00:11:53,128 --> 00:11:54,546
Good job.

132
00:11:55,214 --> 00:11:58,592
Whatever that prosecutor says,
don't give him a reaction.

133
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:01,470
Spare yourself, okay?

134
00:12:03,722 --> 00:12:06,433
It won't do you any good
to antagonize Team A.

135
00:12:25,035 --> 00:12:26,203
You...

136
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:29,540
Darn those bastards!

137
00:12:30,666 --> 00:12:31,875
Hey!

138
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:34,545
Watch your temper already.

139
00:12:35,170 --> 00:12:37,506
Why would you kick my precious baby?

140
00:12:37,589 --> 00:12:38,590
What?

141
00:12:39,299 --> 00:12:41,093
It's still just a toddler.

142
00:12:41,468 --> 00:12:42,970
This is no time to joke around.

143
00:12:43,554 --> 00:12:44,554
Gosh.

144
00:12:44,805 --> 00:12:47,433
Honey, use your brain.

145
00:12:48,016 --> 00:12:49,560
Why would they stop your visit?

146
00:12:49,977 --> 00:12:51,687
Because they know it'll work against them.

147
00:12:53,939 --> 00:12:57,067
To shut Lee Changwoo up?
Does that mean he knows something?

148
00:12:57,901 --> 00:12:58,986
Bingo.

149
00:12:59,069 --> 00:13:00,696
Ah.

150
00:13:00,779 --> 00:13:04,324
Well, I should give it my best shot then.

151
00:13:05,075 --> 00:13:06,160
Yes, it's me.

152
00:13:08,412 --> 00:13:09,788
What?

153
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:14,668
- The Lee Changwoo case files are all gone.
- It makes no sense!

154
00:13:14,877 --> 00:13:17,004
How could they vanish from the archive?

155
00:13:17,087 --> 00:13:19,047
They didn't vanish.

156
00:13:19,131 --> 00:13:22,759
We used an external cleaning service
when we changed archive rooms.

157
00:13:22,843 --> 00:13:26,597
And they burned those records
with some other trash by mistake.

158
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:28,765
It's driving me crazy too.

159
00:13:28,849 --> 00:13:32,352
But everything else is there.
Are you sure no one took them?

160
00:13:32,978 --> 00:13:34,188
Look here.

161
00:13:35,105 --> 00:13:37,316
You shouldn't say such a thing.

162
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:39,193
Why are you trying to cover it up?

163
00:13:39,276 --> 00:13:42,571
Then what else can we do?

164
00:13:42,654 --> 00:13:45,657
Arrest that poor cleaning lady?

165
00:13:45,741 --> 00:13:46,950
Put her in cuffs?

166
00:13:47,784 --> 00:13:51,872
Look, that case was closed
a long time ago, so the record...

167
00:13:51,955 --> 00:13:53,540
You call that an excuse?

168
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:55,876
Goodness.

169
00:13:56,460 --> 00:14:00,631
Whatever. Go write an article
about this if you want.

170
00:14:00,714 --> 00:14:02,341
Suit yourself.

171
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,384
Hey, let's go.

172
00:14:04,843 --> 00:14:07,387
Jeez, she's just unbelievable.

173
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:12,184
Ms. Kim.

174
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,521
Take this.

175
00:14:18,649 --> 00:14:21,193
Hello. Did you hear what happened?

176
00:14:21,276 --> 00:14:25,113
Forget everything else
but the autopsy report...

177
00:14:25,197 --> 00:14:26,490
Even if we get the Adamas,

178
00:14:26,573 --> 00:14:29,034
we need that report
to make the comparison.

179
00:14:30,619 --> 00:14:32,621
AUTOPSY REPORT

180
00:14:33,997 --> 00:14:36,083
- I appreciate your hard work.
- Oh, Mr. Lee.

181
00:14:38,168 --> 00:14:39,836
Where's Mr. Jeong?

182
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:43,382
I ordered him to shred these himself.

183
00:14:43,465 --> 00:14:45,342
Oh, Mr. Kwon summoned him.

184
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:48,053
- Mr. Kwon?
- Yes, sir.

185
00:14:50,597 --> 00:14:52,057
He must be pissed.

186
00:14:52,849 --> 00:14:56,228
Seeing that he skipped me
and summoned Mr. Jeong directly.

187
00:14:59,565 --> 00:15:00,816
Mr. Lee.

188
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:04,069
I did what you asked
and put it on your desk.

189
00:15:35,475 --> 00:15:38,854
I don't know anything. I really don't.

190
00:15:39,771 --> 00:15:44,109
Prosecutor Song asked me
for the Lee Changwoo case records,

191
00:15:44,610 --> 00:15:45,861
but then,

192
00:15:47,237 --> 00:15:48,530
they disappeared.

193
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:52,075
He didn't answer his phone,

194
00:15:52,159 --> 00:15:54,036
so I came here, that's all.

195
00:15:57,789 --> 00:15:59,583
- Mister.
- Yes?

196
00:16:01,251 --> 00:16:02,419
Look at me.

197
00:16:08,383 --> 00:16:10,093
I said, look at me.

198
00:16:18,769 --> 00:16:21,063
Do you think I'm asking where he is

199
00:16:22,439 --> 00:16:24,566
because I really don't know?

200
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:30,405
He has probably heard by now
that the case records have disappeared.

201
00:16:31,156 --> 00:16:32,949
So where would he go next?

202
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:42,751
He'd probably visit his father's grave.

203
00:16:46,338 --> 00:16:48,757
The scar left in his father's skeleton

204
00:16:49,508 --> 00:16:52,344
could replace the missing autopsy report.

205
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:59,434
If you already knew, why did you...

206
00:17:02,771 --> 00:17:04,856
I ask you questions,

207
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:06,900
and you can't answer them.

208
00:17:09,194 --> 00:17:10,404
That way,

209
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:12,781
I can justify myself.

210
00:17:14,950 --> 00:17:16,243
A reason to make a move.

211
00:17:33,009 --> 00:17:34,052
Mister.

212
00:17:35,345 --> 00:17:36,805
Bite down on this.

213
00:17:53,697 --> 00:17:55,615
Our only hope is my father's grave.

214
00:17:56,908 --> 00:17:57,951
For another autopsy?

215
00:17:58,034 --> 00:18:01,163
There should be a scar.
It was stuck in his left eye.

216
00:18:02,706 --> 00:18:04,750
Thank goodness you buried him
in a family gravesite.

217
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:06,293
Your ancestors must be helping.

218
00:18:07,294 --> 00:18:10,714
Darn, they even got rid
of the case records.

219
00:18:10,797 --> 00:18:13,300
Fine, let's fight dirty.

220
00:18:47,375 --> 00:18:48,460
Ms. Oh.

221
00:18:53,757 --> 00:18:55,300
I have a favor to ask of you.

222
00:18:56,718 --> 00:18:59,095
Officially or unofficially?

223
00:19:00,972 --> 00:19:02,974
The latter.

224
00:19:03,558 --> 00:19:04,558
Go on.

225
00:19:05,811 --> 00:19:08,021
I'd like you to get me my bag.

226
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:09,730
Your bag?

227
00:19:09,773 --> 00:19:12,400
Yes, the one I brought
when I came to this house.

228
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:15,612
Oh, they must've taken it from you
for security purposes.

229
00:19:15,695 --> 00:19:17,614
Personal belongings
are not allowed in here.

230
00:19:18,198 --> 00:19:19,574
But why?

231
00:19:21,451 --> 00:19:24,621
Well, I need it for something.

232
00:19:26,498 --> 00:19:29,042
I'm not close
with any security guards here.

233
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:32,546
Sure.

234
00:19:33,088 --> 00:19:37,217
I shouldn't turn down your request.

235
00:19:37,801 --> 00:19:38,969
Thank you.

236
00:19:46,935 --> 00:19:48,061
Between us...

237
00:20:06,413 --> 00:20:08,206
I'm not sure if this is okay.

238
00:20:08,290 --> 00:20:10,458
Don't you want to stop being a house dog?

239
00:20:11,084 --> 00:20:14,337
I promised I'd get you a job
at the head office if you listen to me.

240
00:20:18,216 --> 00:20:19,259
Yes, ma'am.

241
00:20:20,510 --> 00:20:21,803
At your service.

242
00:20:33,398 --> 00:20:34,399
Ms. Oh.

243
00:20:35,442 --> 00:20:37,569
Make sure you keep your promise.

244
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:38,945
Just wait.

245
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:53,417
Eighteen.

246
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:01,342
Twenty.

247
00:21:09,851 --> 00:21:10,851
Do you drink that often?

248
00:21:11,394 --> 00:21:12,394
This?

249
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:14,439
It's good to drink anytime.

250
00:21:19,361 --> 00:21:20,361
I got one for you.

251
00:21:20,779 --> 00:21:22,155
No, thanks.

252
00:21:22,739 --> 00:21:23,739
Have it.

253
00:21:36,044 --> 00:21:39,464
I hope Ms. Kwon likes your novel.

254
00:21:40,173 --> 00:21:44,177
By the way, why are you suddenly
so hung up on her son?

255
00:21:44,260 --> 00:21:47,013
I thought Chairman Kwon killed my father.

256
00:21:48,056 --> 00:21:50,725
Leaving out the time he spent abroad,

257
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:54,145
the statute of limitations was in effect,
so I thought it was worth a shot. But...

258
00:21:54,229 --> 00:21:55,522
But the witness showed up.

259
00:21:56,106 --> 00:21:57,732
Right, Mr. Lee.

260
00:21:58,274 --> 00:22:01,236
If he is the culprit, Chairman Kwon isn't.

261
00:22:01,736 --> 00:22:04,990
Then I wondered
what there could be to punish him with.

262
00:22:05,073 --> 00:22:06,073
Ah.

263
00:22:06,449 --> 00:22:09,035
You want to tie him
to the death of Ms. Kwon's son?

264
00:22:09,619 --> 00:22:11,871
As the culprit of another murder case.

265
00:22:13,581 --> 00:22:14,666
I like that.

266
00:22:17,293 --> 00:22:20,880
It'd be insurance and a means
to tear apart Ms. Kwon and the chairman.

267
00:22:21,131 --> 00:22:22,924
If her loyalty is tested,

268
00:22:23,008 --> 00:22:26,011
she will ease her blind suspicion
against me.

269
00:22:35,729 --> 00:22:37,230
Let me see.

270
00:22:38,398 --> 00:22:40,525
What could be in here?

271
00:22:41,609 --> 00:22:44,154
Why the sudden need for his bag?

272
00:22:45,321 --> 00:22:47,907
What's gotten into him?

273
00:22:50,702 --> 00:22:53,663
What is this? In the Name of Mother?

274
00:22:58,585 --> 00:22:59,711
A novel?

275
00:23:00,295 --> 00:23:02,047
You wrote a story about her son?

276
00:23:02,130 --> 00:23:03,882
Just a few pages.

277
00:23:05,717 --> 00:23:08,762
Ms. Kwon's son attempted suicide
and was declared brain-dead.

278
00:23:10,138 --> 00:23:13,933
Then his heart was transplanted
to Chairman Kwon. Isn't it dramatic?

279
00:23:14,559 --> 00:23:17,187
I wonder how she'll react to that story.

280
00:23:19,064 --> 00:23:20,815
She'll deny it vehemently.

281
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:26,863
And she'll try to see if it's true.

282
00:23:29,574 --> 00:23:32,494
"After painstaking
deliberation, Duke Alfonso"

283
00:23:32,577 --> 00:23:35,121
decided to choose his nanny's only son

284
00:23:35,455 --> 00:23:37,707
"as the suitable donorfor
the heart transplant."

285
00:23:39,918 --> 00:23:43,755
"'It's easier to make a
donorthan to wait for one.'"

286
00:23:44,422 --> 00:23:46,341
Looking at his doctor, Allen,

287
00:23:46,883 --> 00:23:50,470
the duke made a cold smile.

288
00:23:51,596 --> 00:23:54,891
Dr. Allen was satisfied with
the conditionand that night,

289
00:23:55,183 --> 00:23:59,104
"he declared a young man
in a comabrain-dead."

290
00:24:04,984 --> 00:24:08,321
"A loyal nanny would be willing"

291
00:24:09,864 --> 00:24:13,201
"to offer her child's heart to her master."

292
00:24:16,746 --> 00:24:18,790
No...

293
00:24:19,624 --> 00:24:21,709
No.

294
00:24:21,793 --> 00:24:24,003
No, it can't be.

295
00:24:24,879 --> 00:24:25,880
No!

296
00:24:26,798 --> 00:24:28,174
You want to study abroad?

297
00:24:28,258 --> 00:24:30,718
I put you through college.
Wasn't that enough?

298
00:24:30,802 --> 00:24:32,887
Stop dreaming
and just learn to work under me!

299
00:24:34,097 --> 00:24:35,890
You want me to be a servant like you?

300
00:24:35,974 --> 00:24:37,600
A servant? You brat.

301
00:24:39,269 --> 00:24:40,353
Let go.

302
00:24:40,436 --> 00:24:43,398
Mother, you care more about the chairman
than me, don't you?

303
00:24:44,482 --> 00:24:47,485
Of course. I care about the master
way more than you.

304
00:24:47,569 --> 00:24:50,029
Master this, master that!

305
00:24:50,113 --> 00:24:53,533
I'm going to leave.
I'd die before I live the way you do.

306
00:24:54,117 --> 00:24:57,036
What? You won't live like I do?

307
00:24:57,745 --> 00:25:00,498
Fine, die.

308
00:25:00,748 --> 00:25:03,251
Die, you brat.
How could you say that to your mother?

309
00:25:03,334 --> 00:25:06,129
Just go die.

310
00:25:06,212 --> 00:25:08,173
Die!

311
00:25:25,148 --> 00:25:26,191
Hoon!

312
00:25:26,774 --> 00:25:29,569
Hoon! Oh, no.

313
00:25:33,448 --> 00:25:35,450
Hoon!

314
00:25:39,287 --> 00:25:41,873
Hoon...

315
00:26:05,813 --> 00:26:09,317
Please... do as I say.

316
00:26:09,692 --> 00:26:12,654
But, how could I possibly take his heart?

317
00:26:15,615 --> 00:26:16,991
Master, please.

318
00:26:18,451 --> 00:26:19,661
Only then

319
00:26:20,745 --> 00:26:24,165
will I be able to think
Hoon is alive and well by my side.

320
00:26:43,935 --> 00:26:47,438
Ms. Kwon will realize
that the story is about her.

321
00:26:49,774 --> 00:26:52,068
She'll no longer feel
as devoted to the chairman.

322
00:26:53,695 --> 00:26:55,029
It could be dangerous.

323
00:26:55,113 --> 00:26:57,281
What if she talks to him about this?

324
00:26:57,365 --> 00:26:59,742
No, she could never.

325
00:27:01,077 --> 00:27:01,911
Why is that?

326
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:05,373
It'd be a bigger loss for Ms. Kwon.

327
00:27:06,249 --> 00:27:08,084
Chairman Kwon
wouldn't keep her by his side.

328
00:27:10,003 --> 00:27:12,338
Ms. Kwon is quick-witted enough
to know that.

329
00:27:14,424 --> 00:27:15,466
True.

330
00:27:16,217 --> 00:27:18,094
They would suspect each other.

331
00:27:18,177 --> 00:27:20,263
She'd wonder if he killed her son,

332
00:27:20,722 --> 00:27:22,348
and he'd wonder if she suspects him.

333
00:27:22,849 --> 00:27:24,517
A difference in opinion.

334
00:27:25,977 --> 00:27:28,479
It's the beginning of distrust.

335
00:27:29,313 --> 00:27:31,232
I have a question.

336
00:27:33,067 --> 00:27:34,777
You once said...

337
00:27:34,861 --> 00:27:37,089
I need to find out where it's stored
as soon as possible.

338
00:27:37,113 --> 00:27:38,257
Before the recrafting begins.

339
00:27:38,281 --> 00:27:39,615
Should I look into it?

340
00:27:39,699 --> 00:27:41,576
No. Leave it up to us.

341
00:27:43,494 --> 00:27:44,704
"Us."

342
00:27:46,873 --> 00:27:49,167
Is there someone else
helping you other than me?

343
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:56,424
- No.
- In this house or outside?

344
00:27:58,259 --> 00:27:59,259
There's no one else.

345
00:28:04,474 --> 00:28:05,558
There isn't.

346
00:28:11,272 --> 00:28:14,984
You say there isn't anyone,
but I think otherwise.

347
00:28:15,485 --> 00:28:17,445
What do you call this kind of situation?

348
00:28:19,530 --> 00:28:21,491
A difference in opinion.

349
00:28:24,702 --> 00:28:26,704
The beginning of distrust.

350
00:28:29,999 --> 00:28:30,999
Ms. Eun.

351
00:28:31,042 --> 00:28:32,835
You drew the line first.

352
00:28:32,919 --> 00:28:35,129
"I'm not Kwon Minjo."

353
00:28:35,213 --> 00:28:37,298
"I'm not interested
in punishing the chairman."

354
00:28:37,381 --> 00:28:39,717
"We're not after the same thing."
You said so.

355
00:28:43,262 --> 00:28:44,639
Did you change your mind?

356
00:28:49,936 --> 00:28:51,104
What a shame.

357
00:29:04,951 --> 00:29:08,496
It's a lie! A lie...

358
00:29:12,500 --> 00:29:14,293
Ha Woosin...

359
00:29:28,057 --> 00:29:30,017
We've started our process to win her over

360
00:29:30,101 --> 00:29:31,894
by trying to separate her
and the chairman.

361
00:29:31,978 --> 00:29:34,438
But she isn't showing any response yet.

362
00:29:35,106 --> 00:29:37,150
We'll see how it goes and act accordingly.

363
00:29:37,233 --> 00:29:38,234
Okay.

364
00:29:39,026 --> 00:29:42,446
We're also taking two measures
in case Mr. Ha's plan falls through.

365
00:29:42,530 --> 00:29:45,700
We're trying to figure out
where Ms. Jang, the jewelry designer, is.

366
00:29:45,825 --> 00:29:47,425
We were too focused on the task at hand.

367
00:29:48,286 --> 00:29:51,414
Team A took Lee Changwoo's case file.

368
00:29:51,497 --> 00:29:54,167
What? Even the autopsy report?

369
00:29:55,668 --> 00:29:58,004
What on earth?
Then all this would've been for nothing.

370
00:29:58,087 --> 00:29:59,964
Now the remaining option is...

371
00:30:15,438 --> 00:30:16,731
Something's off.

372
00:30:18,316 --> 00:30:19,734
It hasn't taken root yet.

373
00:30:20,234 --> 00:30:21,360
It was planted recently.

374
00:30:22,987 --> 00:30:25,865
What, those punks already came here?

375
00:30:26,199 --> 00:30:28,159
And dug up this grave to...

376
00:30:29,035 --> 00:30:30,161
To vandalize his body.

377
00:30:33,706 --> 00:30:34,999
I'm getting the creeps.

378
00:30:35,499 --> 00:30:37,001
Wait, let me think.

379
00:30:37,668 --> 00:30:40,463
Now, even if we get our hands
on the Adamas,

380
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:42,560
we won't have anything to compare it with.

381
00:30:43,132 --> 00:30:44,550
This is terrible.

382
00:30:45,551 --> 00:30:47,637
How are we going to prove
it was used for the murder?

383
00:30:49,347 --> 00:30:50,681
Was it Woosin?

384
00:30:51,766 --> 00:30:52,600
What?

385
00:30:52,683 --> 00:30:54,936
This grave isn't my father's.

386
00:30:56,520 --> 00:30:58,856
- What?
- An old man lived alone in our village.

387
00:30:58,940 --> 00:31:00,316
My father buried him here.

388
00:31:00,900 --> 00:31:03,569
He'd tidy up the grave
and hold a memorial service for him.

389
00:31:04,070 --> 00:31:05,947
The gravestone was switched.

390
00:31:08,950 --> 00:31:10,952
He knew Haesong would damage the body.

391
00:31:11,953 --> 00:31:14,330
Since the strongest evidence
in a murder case

392
00:31:14,956 --> 00:31:16,540
is the victim himself.

393
00:31:17,750 --> 00:31:20,962
But who? Who expected
this would happen and changed gravestones?

394
00:31:21,462 --> 00:31:22,672
Isn't it obvious?

395
00:31:26,300 --> 00:31:27,718
This one is my father's.

396
00:31:47,029 --> 00:31:48,698
I'll make sure to catch the culprit.

397
00:31:50,908 --> 00:31:52,410
For you, Father.

398
00:31:54,745 --> 00:31:56,122
And for him.

399
00:31:59,417 --> 00:32:00,334
PUNISHMENT

400
00:32:00,418 --> 00:32:04,005
Whatever that prosecutor says,
don't give him a reaction.

401
00:32:04,547 --> 00:32:06,007
Spare yourself, okay?

402
00:32:06,674 --> 00:32:08,926
It won't do you any
goodto antagonize Team A.

403
00:32:13,681 --> 00:32:15,182
We're good for the time being.

404
00:32:15,850 --> 00:32:18,311
Team A would believe
that they damaged the body.

405
00:32:19,020 --> 00:32:21,147
That punk. He's always one step ahead.

406
00:32:21,314 --> 00:32:22,398
You mean your brother?

407
00:32:23,274 --> 00:32:25,401
If he were a soccer player,
he would've made it big.

408
00:32:26,652 --> 00:32:29,989
By the way, what's your name?
I don't even know your name yet.

409
00:32:30,614 --> 00:32:32,700
In my line of work,
we don't introduce ourselves.

410
00:32:33,743 --> 00:32:37,288
We don't know when we'll die,
so it's no use making friends.

411
00:32:37,830 --> 00:32:39,874
It's not like we'll die together.

412
00:32:40,082 --> 00:32:42,585
Just call me "Mr. Baek."

413
00:32:43,419 --> 00:32:46,630
I'm sheepish with calling you Mr. Baek.

414
00:32:48,424 --> 00:32:50,426
Want a beating, honey?

415
00:32:51,010 --> 00:32:53,054
How about just Baek?

416
00:32:54,096 --> 00:32:56,182
Baek? It's not bad.

417
00:32:58,809 --> 00:33:00,269
I'm hearing something.

418
00:33:03,439 --> 00:33:04,690
Hear what?

419
00:33:05,024 --> 00:33:06,359
I think a phone's ringing.

420
00:33:25,002 --> 00:33:26,002
Should I open it?

421
00:33:40,309 --> 00:33:41,435
Oh, my.

422
00:34:17,805 --> 00:34:19,932
Those crazy bastards...

423
00:34:20,015 --> 00:34:22,351
- No, wait.
- Let go of me.

424
00:34:35,531 --> 00:34:36,949
Pick up.

425
00:34:39,201 --> 00:34:40,911
Pick up the phone.

426
00:34:53,090 --> 00:34:54,467
Who are you?

427
00:34:55,134 --> 00:34:57,470
Who... Who are you?

428
00:34:58,679 --> 00:35:00,055
Who are you?

429
00:35:05,102 --> 00:35:06,145
Sun.

430
00:35:16,363 --> 00:35:17,363
Boom.

431
00:35:30,252 --> 00:35:34,131
You at least needed to know
who was killing you.

432
00:35:36,091 --> 00:35:39,011
Now I feel bad.

433
00:35:43,140 --> 00:35:44,183
Mr. Ha.

434
00:35:46,894 --> 00:35:48,020
We have a serious problem.

435
00:35:52,691 --> 00:35:54,401
I think Ms. Kwon has finally gone insane.

436
00:35:54,568 --> 00:35:56,820
She's yelling out loudly, asking for you.

437
00:35:56,904 --> 00:35:58,697
She's absolutely lost her mind.

438
00:36:00,574 --> 00:36:03,869
Her eyes are flipping out
as if she's ready to kill someone.

439
00:36:04,537 --> 00:36:08,082
Just what have you done this time?
I feel so anxious

440
00:36:09,833 --> 00:36:11,335
that it's killing me, seriously.

441
00:36:22,179 --> 00:36:23,222
Ms. Kwon?

442
00:36:28,477 --> 00:36:29,562
Ms. Kwon.

443
00:36:31,605 --> 00:36:33,023
Did you ask for me?

444
00:36:34,525 --> 00:36:36,068
Mr. Ha.

445
00:36:37,361 --> 00:36:39,905
I didn't like you from the start.

446
00:36:40,739 --> 00:36:42,950
Your eyes told me
that you were hiding something.

447
00:36:43,450 --> 00:36:45,703
Those eyes bothered me.

448
00:36:46,787 --> 00:36:49,164
I'm hiding something? Me?

449
00:36:49,248 --> 00:36:51,542
Your true motive for coming to this house.

450
00:36:53,627 --> 00:36:55,087
I'm not really following.

451
00:36:57,673 --> 00:36:59,508
Drop your clumsy act.

452
00:37:01,343 --> 00:37:03,929
You came here
to write a story about my son.

453
00:37:04,013 --> 00:37:05,806
You needed information to do that.

454
00:37:09,768 --> 00:37:10,894
Ah.

455
00:37:11,604 --> 00:37:13,105
Ah.

456
00:37:13,188 --> 00:37:14,607
Ah?

457
00:37:17,026 --> 00:37:18,277
Let me explain.

458
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:20,279
No, you don't have to.

459
00:37:20,779 --> 00:37:24,199
I've read your incredulous story.

460
00:37:26,076 --> 00:37:28,537
You've read it?
You mean the manuscript in my bag?

461
00:37:28,621 --> 00:37:29,705
Yes.

462
00:37:30,914 --> 00:37:31,914
Ah.

463
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:34,293
So you have.

464
00:37:43,636 --> 00:37:45,137
I guess I can't hide it anymore.

465
00:37:46,764 --> 00:37:49,391
You're right. I came to this house

466
00:37:49,475 --> 00:37:51,894
because of what happened to your son.

467
00:37:55,356 --> 00:37:56,815
It's quite interesting.

468
00:37:58,734 --> 00:37:59,985
Interesting?

